--->\n<ref name=wright-07>{{cite journal| last=Wright| first=Michael T.| date=2007| title=The Antikythera Mechanism reconsidered| doi=10.1179/030801807X163670| journal=Interdisciplinary Science Reviews| volume=32| number=1| pages=21\u201343| url=https://semanticscholar.org/paper/90fd0243621cd7480d0f61927e5f20805fadbab9}}</ref>\n<ref name=cicero>{{cite web| url=http://www.thelatinlibrary.com/cicero/repub1.shtml#21| title=M. TVLLI CICERONIS DE RE PVBLICA LIBER PRIMVS| accessdate=23 March 2007| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070322054142/http://www.thelatinlibrary.com/cicero/repub1.shtml#21| archivedate=22 March 2007| url-status=dead| df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n<ref name=rorres-11>{{cite web| url=http://www.math.nyu.edu/~crorres/Archimedes/Sphere/SphereIntro.html| publisher=New York University| first=Chris| last=Rorres| accessdate=27 March 2011| title=Archimedes: Spheres and Planetaria (Introduction)| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110510050414/http://www.math.nyu.edu/~crorres/Archimedes/Sphere/SphereIntro.html| archivedate=10 May 2011| url-status=dead| df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n<ref name=fildes-10>{{Cite news| last=Fildes| first=Jonathan| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/sci/tech/6191462.stm| work=BBC News| title=Ancient Moon 'computer' revisited| date=29 November 2006| accessdate=25 April 2010}}</ref>\n<ref name=needham>{{cite book| last=Needham| title=Needham| volume=4, Part | page=285}}</ref>\n<ref name=sleeswyk-81>{{cite news| first1=Andre| last1=Sleeswyk| title=Vitruvius' odometer| periodical=Scientific American| volume=252| number=4| pages=188\u2013200| date=October 1981}}See also: Andre Wegener Sleeswyk, \"Vitruvius' waywiser\", ''Archives internationales d'histoire des sciences'', vol. 29, pages 11\u201322 (1979).</ref>\n<ref name=cicero-1>{{cite web| url=http://www.thelatinlibrary.com/cicero/nd2.shtml#88| title=Cicero, De Natura Deorum II.88 (or 33\u201334)| accessdate=23 March 2007| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070316053820/http://www.thelatinlibrary.com/cicero/nd2.shtml#88| archivedate=16 March 2007| url-status=dead| df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n<ref name=charette-06>Archaeology: High tech from Ancient Greece, Fran\u00e7ois Charette, ''Nature'' 444, #7119 (30 November 2006), pp. 551\u2013552, {{doi| 10.1038/444551a}}.</ref>\n<ref name=madison-85>{{cite journal| title=Early mathematical wheelwork: Byzantine calendrical gearing| first=Francis| last=Maddison| journal=Nature| volume=314| issue=6009| date=28 March 1985| pages=316\u2013317| doi=10.1038/314316b0|bibcode = 1985Natur.314..316M }}.</ref>\n<ref name=amrp-12>{{cite web| url=http://www.antikythera-mechanism.gr/events/exhibitions/nam-2012| title=The Antikythera Shipwreck: the Ship, the Treasures, the Mechanism| publisher=Antikythera Mechanism Research Project| date=6 June 2012| accessdate=16 April 2013}}</ref>\n<ref name=imdb>{{cite web| url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1918031/| title=Naked Science &ndash; Star Clock BC (TV Episode)| year=2011}}{{unreliable source?|date=August 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=amrp-movie>{{cite web| url=http://www.antikythera-mechanism.gr/media/movies/worlds-first-computer| title=The World's First Computer| publisher=Antikythera Mechanism Research Project| accessdate=21 January 2013}}</ref>\n<ref name=amrp-movie-bbc>{{cite web| url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b01hlkcq| title=BBC Four - The Two-Thousand-Year-Old Computer}}</ref>\n<ref name=amrp-movie-nova>{{cite episode| series=NOVA| network=PBS| url=http://www.pbs.org/wgbh/nova/ancient/ancient-computer.html| title=Ancient Computer| accessdate=13 May 2014}}</ref>\n<ref name=stonehenge>{{cite web| url=http://watchinghorrorfilmsfrombehindthecouch.blogspot.ca/2011/05/stonehenge-apocalypse.html| title=Behind The Couch: 'Stonehenge Apocalypse'| last=Gracey| first=James| date=23 May 2011| publisher=BehindTheCouch web site| accessdate=23 May 2011}}</ref>\n<ref name=pavlus>{{cite web| last=Pavlus| first=John| title=Small Mammal, Behind the Scenes: Lego Antikythera Mechanism| url=https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=RLPVCJjTNgk| publisher=Small Mammal| accessdate=19 July 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=amrp-exhib>{{cite web| title=Exhibitions| url=http://www.antikythera-mechanism.gr/events/exhibitions| publisher=The Antikythera Mechanism Research Project}}</ref>\n}}\n\n==Further reading==\n===Books===\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite book|last1=Lin|first1=Jian-Liang|last2=Yan|first2=Hong-Sen|title=Decoding the Mechanisms of Antikythera Astronomical Device|date=2016|publisher=Springer|location=Berlin [u.a.]|isbn=9783662484456}}\n* {{cite book|last1=Jones|first1=Alexander|title=A Portable Cosmos: Revealing the Antikythera Mechanism, Scientific Wonder of the Ancient World|date=2017|publisher=Oxford University Press|location=Oxford|isbn=9780199739349}}\n* {{Cite journal|title=The Inscriptions of the Antikythera Mechanism |journal=Almagest (Turnhout, Belgium) |date=2016 |publisher=Brepols Publishers |series=Almagest 7.1 |location=Turnhout |issn=1792-2593 |author =Allen, M. |author2=Ambrisco, W. |author3=e.a. }}\n* {{Cite book|title=Decoding the Heavens: Solving the Mystery of the World's First Computer |first=Jo |date=6 November 2008 |publisher=William Heinemann Ltd.|isbn=978-0-434-01835-2 |last=Marchant }}\n* {{Cite book|title=The Forgotten Revolution: How Science Was Born in 300 BC and Why It Had To Be Reborn |first=Lucio |date=2004 |publisher=Springer |isbn=978-3-540-20396-4 |location = Berlin |last=Russo | authorlink = Lucio Russo }}\n* {{Cite book| title=Observations and Predictions of Eclipse Times by Early Astronomers | date=2000 | publisher=Kluwer Academic | isbn=978-0-7923-6298-2 | location=Dordrecht| author=Steele, J. M. }}\n* {{Cite book|title=Ptolemy's Almagest | date=1998 | publisher=Princeton Univ. Press |others=Translated by Toomer, G. J. |location=Princeton, New Jersey | author = Toomer, G. J. |authorlink=Gerald J. Toomer}}\n* {{Cite book| title=Historical Eclipses and the Earth's Rotation | date=1997 | publisher=Cambridge Univ. Press | isbn=978-0-521-46194-8 | 